  "prompt": "Why do I always feel sleepy in college lectures?",
  "response": "There are several reasons why you might feel sleepy during college lectures:\n\n1. Lack of sleep\n- Irregular sleep schedule\n- Not getting enough hours of sleep\n- Poor sleep quality\n\n2. Lecture environment\n- Dim lighting\n- Warm room temperature\n- Comfortable seating\n- Monotonous speaking style of the lecturer\n\n3. Attention and engagement\n- Complex or uninteresting subject matter\n- Passive learning style\n- Difficulty understanding the content\n\n4. Physiological factors\n- Poor nutrition\n- Dehydration\n- Sedentary lifestyle\n- Medical conditions like sleep apnea\n\n5. Circadian rhythm\n- Morning classes might conflict with your natural sleep cycle\n- Some people are naturally less alert during certain times of the day\n\nTips to stay awake:\n- Get adequate sleep\n- Stay hydrated\n- Eat a balanced diet\n- Take active notes\n- Sit near the front of the class\n- Move or stretch periodically\n- Engage with the material\n- Consider caffeine in moderation\n- Get regular exercise\n\nIf sleepiness persists, consult a healthcare professional to rule out underlying health issues.",
